title: atlanta_class_light_cruiser
body: An 'anti-aircraft cruiser' originally intended to replace the Omaha class (in terms of tonnage classification as determined by treaties of the era). One of the few classes of warships to have super-superimposed turret arraignment (although that led to some top weight issues). Designed to lead destroyers squadrons their main armament was the same as those of destroyers (although they have many more guns). Generally a somewhat lackluster design although they actually had a rather comprehensive ASW suite (although their lack of maneuverability compared to destroyers made that a moot point).

title: jin_yong
body:
[b]Louis Cha Jing-yon[/b] (10 March 1924 – 30 October 2018), better known by his pen name [b]Jin Yong[/b], was a Chinese wuxia ("martial arts and chivalry") novelist and essayist who co-founded the Hong Kong daily newspaper Ming Pao in 1959 and served as its first editor-in-chief. He was Hong Kong's most famous writer.

His wuxia novels have a widespread following in Chinese communities worldwide. His 15 works written between 1955 and 1972 earned him a reputation as one of the greatest and most popular wuxia writers ever. By the time of his death he was the best-selling Chinese author, and over 100 million copies of his works have been sold worldwide (not including an unknown number of pirated copies).

body:
[b][i]Neuromancer[/i][/b] is a 1984 [[science fiction]] novel by "William Gibson":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Gibson , a seminal work in the [[cyberpunk]] subgenre and the first winner of the sci-fi "triple crown" — the Nebula Award, the [[Philip K. Dick]] Award, and the Hugo Award. It was Gibson's debut novel and the beginning of the "Sprawl Trilogy". 

Set in a dystopic future, the novel tells the story of a washed-up [[computer]] hacker hired by a mysterious employer to pull off the ultimate hack. The original book's cover created by Rick Berry in 1984 was the world's first digitally painted [[book]] cover.

The book also won the 1987 "Seiun award":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seiun_Award for best translated foreign novel in Japan.

title: matsuno_todomatsu
body:
[quote]
For a type of [[tree]] called todo-matsu (椴松) in Japanese, use [[sakhalin fir]].
[/quote]

A character from [i][[Osomatsu-kun]][/i] and its spin-offs. His name is a wordplay for the Japanese term of "'in the end'":[http://tangorin.com/general/todonotsumari] and "[[sakhalin fir]]". 

He is the youngest of the Matsuno [[sextuplets]], characterized by his easygoing and carefree attitude. In [i][[Osomatsu-san]][/i], he retains this personality trait, but becomes the socializer of the brothers and gains some feminine characteristics. As a side effect, he has the most luck in talking to women. He tends to be secretive about his life outside the house, and has the most scheming personality out of his siblings due to wanting to elevate his social status.

He is characterized with his large eyes and [[:3]] expression in [i]Osomatsu-san[/i]. He is associated with the color pink.

title: matsuno_ichimatsu
body:
[quote]
For a type of pattern called ichimatsu-moyou, see [[checkered]].
[/quote]

A character from [i][[Osomatsu-kun]][/i] and its spin-offs.

He is the fourth born son of the Matsuno [[sextuplets]], characterized by his honesty and strength second to [[matsuno_osomatsu|the eldest brother]]. In [i][[Osomatsu-san]][/i] he becomes lazy and apathetic, and  has the most trouble communicating to people. He also has an affinity for [[cat]]s.

He can usually be told apart from his brothers by his [[messy hair]] and [[jitome]] in [i]Osomatsu-san[/i]. He is associated with the color purple.

title: wolfgang_krauser
body:
A reoccurring [[SNK]] boss character in the [[Fatal Fury]] and [[The King of Fighters]] series, Krauser is the [[brothers|half-brother]] of [[Geese Howard]]. Notable traits of his include his [[purple hair]], [[breastplate|golden chestplate]], and an [[Cross Scar|X-Shaped]] [[scar]] on his forehead.

Krauser is a powerful fighter who is eager to fight strong opponents. In [[Fatal Fury 2]], he arranges his own King of Fighters tournament, in hopes of fighting strong opponents. He injures several veteran fighters from the previous King of Fighters tournament and he also hires three fighters to serve him who are [[Billy Kane]], [[Axel Hawk]], and [[Laurence Blood]]. Eventually, he fights [[Terry Bogard]] in the finals. After a fierce battle, Krauser is defeated and remains missing from the fighting scene. [spoiler] According to the short movie, Memories of Stray Wolves, Krauser supposedly took his own life soon after. [/spoiler]

In The King of Fighters series, nothing was heard of from Krauser until [[The King of Fighters '96]] tournament, when Krauser joined forces with Geese and [[mr big (snk)|Mr. Big]] to create the Boss Team. Although Geese used both him and Mr. Big as pawns in his attempt to nab an ancient power called [[orochi (kof)|Orochi]], Krauser only cared about self-improvement. After learning of his faults at the hands of Terry, Krauser vowed only to fight stronger opponents in order to restore the strength and prestige he once possessed. For now, Krauser wants only to improve himself first.

* The infamous SNK boss and King of Fighters character; [[Rugal Bernstein]], uses one of Krauser's signature moves, the [b][i][i]Kaiser Wave[/i][/i][/b].
* His debut theme is "Dies Irae":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dies_Irae.
* He is one of the only SNK characters to be fully voiced in English by an English voice actor (B.J. Love). 

h4.See Also

* "Wolfgang Krauser Article - SNK Wiki":http://snk.wikia.com/wiki/Wolfgang_Krauser?useskin=oasis

Character from [[Shinrabanshou]]'s 2010 storyline, the Zex Factor chapter. title: star_dream
body:
A seemingly malevolent A.I. that serves as the true antagonist and final boss of [i][[Kirby: Planet Robobot]][/i]. It is the so-called "Mother Computer" that runs most if not all of the operations of the Haltmann Works Company.

When [[max_profitt_haltmann|President Haltmann]] resorts to using it to defeat [[Kirby]], [[susie_(kirby)|Susie]] attempts to steal the computer from him for her own benefit. Star Dream, having slowly gained sentience from Haltmann over time, quickly retaliates and gains control of Haltmann's mind.

With a newfound soul, it combines Haltmann's wish for prosperity with an unknown desire for destruction to carry out an attack to destroy all organic life in the universe. It takes the combined efforts of Kirby, his [[Robobot Armor]], and the [[halberd_(airship)|Halberd]] (courtesy of [[Meta Knight]]) to take it down and save the day once more.

[spoiler]An interesting thing to note is that as the Halberd wears down the Mother Computer's defenses, it shows its true form: A cat-like mechanical comet. This along with [[marx_soul|Marx Soul's]] flavor text and [[magolor|Magolor's]] mention of "clockwork stars" very heavily implies that Star Dream, along with [[Galactic Nova]], are only two of many wish-granting, godlike machines created by an ancient civilization.

title: aoi_hana
body:
[b]Aoi Hana[/b] (青い花) is a [[yuri]] manga by [[Shimura Takako]]. Original run: 2004–2013. There is also a 2009 TV anime adaptation.

The Japanese manga tankoubon release covers also give an English title, [i]Sweet Blue Flowers[/i].

JManga published at least parts of the manga series online in official English translation around 2012–2013, but these are probably no more available. An official English-subtitled online version of the anime has been released by Crunchyroll.com.

Themes include lesbian and bisexual adolescence, love and friendship, girls'-school life, and amateur theater.

title: zorua
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #570 in the National PokéDex, a Dark type Pokémon.
Zorua is a slate gray, fox-like Pokémon with red and black accents. Its ears are triangular with dark insides, and it has a large tuft of fur tipped with red on top of its head. It has greenish blue eyes with red eyelids. There are circular, red markings above the eyes that resemble eyebrows. Its muzzle is short and tapered with two small fangs seen in the upper jaw when its mouth is open.

One of the first [[pokemon|Pokémon]] revealed to appear in the fifth main installment of the Pokémon franchise. The fox-like Pokémon is a Dark-type that evolves into [[Zoroark]]. It uses its Illusion ability [[disguised_zorua|to disguise itself as other Pokémon]]. A Zorua took the central role in the thirteenth [[pokemon_(anime)|Pokémon movie]].

It evolves into [[Zoroark]].

title: uss_indianapolis_(ca-35)
body:
Second ship of the Portland class, served as Fifth Fleet Flagship during WWII. Delivered the [[nuclear weapon|nuclear bomb]] in 1945 to Tinian island, was sunk soon afterwards, having the unfortunate distinction of being the last major US war loss of WWII. Due to a number of miscommunication the survivors were left drifting in shark infested water for days before being rescued. Her captain was unfairly tried and found guilty of losing his ship, the guilt of which led to his suicide a decade later. Was finally exonerated when some high school kid did a research project on the whole event during the 90s.

It is unknown exactly what's inside the bucket, though in the anime it's a magical liquid that can cause a ship girl to experience intense pleasure as a side effect of its use.

The tag can be used on containers [i]based[/i] on the repair bucket (e.g. as a [[drinking glass]] on post #2453713 and as an [[ice cream]] tub on post #2364987) as it is not currently implicated to "[[bucket]]". (see topic #13619)

title: nosuri
body:
Nosuri is the leader of the Nosuri bandits, a gang of righteous thieves. After an incident involving Anju, the crown princess of Yamato, she is forced to work with Haku's team. She is revealed to be the daughter of the deposed chieftain of Izuruha, leading her to become the next chieftain. While she might be knuckleheaded, she has a good heart and with this (plus the aforementioned mishap), she gained the implicit trust of Anju as her liege.

Nosuri is from an offshoot Evenkuruga clan in Yamato. Thus, she is of the same race as Touka and Genjimaru and has the same core values.
